headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 37 points and 13 rebounds, James Harden scored 29 points in his first game in Brooklyn since being traded a year ago to begin a Big Three breakup, and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Nets 101-98 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid leads 76ers over Nets in Harden's return to Brooklyn

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 30 points, 16 rebounds and 10 assists for his league-leading 20th triple-double and the short-handed Denver Nuggets handed the Charlotte Hornets their seventh straight defeat, 119-105 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic carries short-handed Nuggets past Hornets 119-105

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 23 points, Jimmy Butler added 22 points and seven rebounds and the Miami Heat rallied to beat the Orlando Magic 107-103 in overtime on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat use balanced scoring, rally to beat Magic 107-103 in OT

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal scored 32 points, Kristaps Porzingis and Monte Morris added 17 apiece and the Washington Wizards shot 70% from the field through the first three quarters of their 127-113 rout of the Indiana Pacers on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sharp-shooting Wizards score 80 in half, rout Pacers 127-113

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Trae Young had 24 points and a season-high 17 assists, De’Andre Hunter added 24 points and the Atlanta Hawks beat the reeling San Antonio Spurs 125-106 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young, Hunter pace Hawks past reeling Spurs 125-106

events.name: Utah Jazz at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson scored 22 of his 38 points in the first half, Josh Hart had 11 points off the bench in his Knicks debut and New York outlasted the Utah Jazz 126-120 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson scores 38 as Knicks outlast Jazz in Hart's NY debut

headlines.description: — All-Star Donovan Mitchell scored 19 of his 29 points in the second half and Jarrett Allen had 23 points and 10 rebounds, rallying the Cleveland Cavaliers to a 97-89 victory over the Chicago Bulls on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell nets 29 as Cavs rally past Bulls, win streak hits 6

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — D’Angelo Russell and the new-look Lakers figured things out on the fly to take down the defending champs on their home floor.
headlines.shortLinkText: Russell shines in return to Lakers after trade by T-Wolves

headlines.description: — De'Aaron Fox scored 36 points, including six free throws in the final 18.4 seconds of overtime, leading the Sacramento Kings to a 133-128 victory over the Dallas Mavericks on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox scores 36 points, Kings beat Mavericks 133-128 in OT
